</div><p itemprop="name"><img src="/sierrasuntimes/images/2021/july/bluefire712021modismap.jpg" alt="bluefire712021modismap" /><br />MODIS map of the Blue Fire on Thursday at 6:00 A.M. PST&nbsp;<br />Note: 1,200 Wide<br /><strong><strong><a itemprop="url" href="https://goldrushcam.com/sierrasuntimes/index.php/news/local-news/14597-modis-active-fire-mapping-program-frequently-asked-questions">MODIS Active Fire Mapping Program Frequently Asked Questions</a></strong></strong></p>
<hr />
<p itemprop="name">July 1, 2021 -&nbsp;<strong>Thursday Evening Update:&nbsp;400 Acres with 75% Containment</strong><br /><br /><img src="/sierrasuntimes/images/2021/july/bluefire700.jpg" alt="bluefire700" /><br /><br /></p>
<hr />
<p itemprop="name"><strong>Thursday Afternoon Update:&nbsp;400 Acres with 25% Containment</strong><br /><br /><br /><button type="button" data-toggle="collapse" aria-expanded="false" data-target="#IncidentInformation" aria-controls="IncidentInformation">
<h2>Incident Information</h2>
<div></div>
</button></p>
<div id="IncidentInformation">
<div>
<div>
<h3>Basic Information</h3>
<table summary="This table displays high level information about the incident">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td scope="row">Current as of</td>
<td>7/1/2021, 5:24:13 PM</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td scope="row">Incident Type</td>
<td>Wildfire</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td scope="row">Cause</td>
<td>Unknown</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td scope="row">Date of Origin</td>
<td>Tuesday June 29th, 2021 approx. 04:30 PM</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td scope="row">Location</td>
<td>The Blue fire is located forty-three miles northeast of Clovis, CA, West of Bretz Mill Campground in Blue Canyon on the High Sierra Ranger District.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td scope="row">Incident Commander</td>
<td>USFSCA-SNF Vic Lafor IC3 Trainee, Joaquin Marquez IC 3</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td scope="row">Incident Description</td>
<td>Fire Burning In Timber, Understory Litter, And Short Grass. Active Moderate Rate Of Spread With Single Tree And Group Torching With Short Crown Runs Being Observed.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td scope="row">Coordinates</td>
<td>37.033 latitude, -119.258 longitude</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<div>
<h3>Current Situation</h3>
<table summary="This table displays the situation information.">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td scope="row">Total Personnel</td>
<td>175</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td scope="row">Size</td>
<td>400 Acres</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td scope="row">Percent of Perimeter Contained</td>
<td>25%</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td scope="row">Fuels Involved</td>
<td>
<p>Timber, understory litter, short grasses</p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<div>
<h3>Outlook</h3>
<table summary="This table displays outlook information.">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td scope="row">Planned Actions</td>
<td>
<p>Today crews are optimistic in their efforts to gain ground and more containment on the Blue Fire. Actions planned are to continue to build handline and dozer line supported by helicopter water drops. Strengthen and maintain containment where fire activity is threatening to escape containment lines. Go direct in attack on areas where line is needing attention, and begin mop up operations.</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td scope="row">Projected Incident Activity</td>
<td>
<p>Continue to build, strengthen and secure handline mop-up where appropriate.</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td scope="row">Remarks</td>
<td>
<p>General situation awareness: The fire is burning in a area where it is critically dry with receptive fuel (vegetation) beds, this is in an active area for fire history and drought stressed trees.</p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<div>
<h3>Current Weather</h3>
<table summary="This table displays weather information.">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td scope="row">Weather Concerns</td>
<td>
<p>Weather over the fire are will be mostly clear during the day with high temperatures in between 82-87 degrees, Min. humidity levels 27-32 percent, winds 5-6 MPH westerly over the surrounding ridge.</p>
<p>Concern: Another round of convection is possible this afternoon over the fire area as instability remains in place with the potential for erratic thunderstorm outflow winds, this instability will drop with the the setting sun. Friday we will see less convection as the upper level flow shifts to the southwest. Winds will be light and terrain driven, except for the chance of thunderstorm outflow winds.</p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
</div>
</div>
